# Banned-pattern template for pre-commit / commit-msg hooks.
#
# On a fresh clone:
#   1. cp .git-banned-patterns.example .git-banned-patterns
#   2. Uncomment and edit the lines below with patterns you want to block.
#   3. Run: git config core.hooksPath hooks
#
# Rules:
#   - One pattern per line.
#   - Lines starting with `#` and blank lines are ignored.
#   - Matching is case-insensitive substring (grep -i -F).
#   - Patterns may include spaces and non-ASCII (UTF-8) characters.
#   - `.git-banned-patterns` itself is gitignored — your patterns never leave your clone.
#
# Examples (uncomment and replace with your own values):
#
# Full name (English, lowercase form will match upper too):
# yamada taro
#
# Full name (Japanese):
# 山田太郎
#
# Conversational nickname or handle that should not appear in commits/code:
# nickname-here
#
# Student / employee ID:
# A12345
#
# Affiliation details that should stay out of public repos:
# example university chemistry department
